ories; and extended protection plans and repair services. Further, the company provides design, distribution, and installation services for interior surface finishes to home builders and property managers. It sells its national brand-name merchandise and private brand products to professional customers, individual homeowners, and renters. The company serves its products through Lowes.com website, mobile applications, retail home improvement stores and outlet stores, and its branches. Lowe's Companies, Inc. was founded in 1921 and is based in Mooresville, North Carolina.","industry":"Home Improvement Retail","sector":"Consumer Cyclical","marketCap":116458856448,"trailingPE":17.542229,"forwardPE":15.423355,"pegRatio":1.4,"priceToBook":null,"priceToSales":1.3169013,"profitMargin":7.510000499999999,"operatingMargin":11.067,"grossMargin":33.293,"returnOnEquity":null,"returnOnAssets":12.792,"revenueGrowthYoy":10.299999999999999,"earningsGrowthYoy":-0.7000000000000001,"earningsQuarterlyGrowthYoy":-0.8,"debtToEquity":null,"currentRatio":1.093,"quickRatio":0.096,"freeCashFlow":4816124928,"operatingCashFlow":9834999808,"totalCash":786000000,"totalDebt":42555998208,"revenue":88433999872,"dividendYield":2.41,"payoutRatio":40.57,"beta":0.904,"fiftyTwoWeekHigh":293.06,"fiftyTwoWeekLow":207.55,"targetMeanPrice":263.72726,"targetHighPrice":300,"targetLowPrice":202,"recommendationKey":"buy","numberOfAnalystOpinions":33,"lastQuarter":{"date":"2026-04-30","period":"-1q","epsActual":3.03,"epsEstimate":2.967,"surprisePct":2.12},"earningsHistory":[{"date":"2025-07-31","period":"-4q","epsActual":4.33,"epsEstimate":4.23777,"surprisePct":2.18},{"date":"2025-10-31","period":"-3q","epsActual":3.06,"epsEstimate":2.9534,"surprisePct":3.61},{"date":"2026-01-31","period":"-2q","epsActual":1.98,"epsEstimate":1.94244,"surprisePct":1.9299999},{"date":"2026-04-30","period":"-1q","epsActual":3.03,"epsEstimate":2.967,"surprisePct":2.12}],"revenueHistory":[{"date":"2025-04-30","value":20930000000},{"dat